The paper deals with privacy and security in a payment splitting app, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of a protocol that involves updating balances and computing integrity checks, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of an Android app and a server, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of a protocol that requires no cryptographic operations on the server, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
